Ask HN: Has anyone switched from Chrome to Edge to play with the new AI stuff?
text:
I recently set up Edge just to play around with the new Bing AI Chat, and was surprised to see they've got all kinds of interesting plugins and widgets they've created. There's a math equation solver, various web capture stuff, a built in image editor, the Bing Chat in the sidebar, some kind of AI "Visual Search" thing I can't figure out, etc. I've been out of the MS loop for a really long time and was pretty surprised to see how good it's looking.

It looks really polished and they make it easy to import extensions and etc from Chrome, so I've given it a try. Has anyone else switched, have any thoughts on this? Is there some drawback I'm not aware of?

I'm not used to MS being so far ahead of the pack on features like this! Very bizarre.

Ask HN: How many jobs LLMs have replaced in your company?
text:
Maybe it is already asked but just wanted to get a sense of the impact these generative AI models have including Stable diffusion etc.

They might have made some jobs easier by giving a head start but have they totally replaced some jobs such as technical writers, customer support or graphics designers to the point of making some to pack their stuff and leave the desk?

The recent inflation/over hiring/preventive layouts don't count.
